“Staying in the present moment, even when it’s uncomfortable, is one of the best ways to gain a healthy mindset. And creativity is such a powerful tool for my mental health. Moving into a creative place when you are feeling uncomfortable-instead of reacting in the moment-gives you the space you need to pass through the negativity and come out the other side.”

- excerpt from my book, Mindful Sketching: How to Develop a Drawing Practice & Embrace the Art of Imperfection

